description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a Health Care Assistant to support our physical health/ depot clinic services in Brighton and Hove.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a person with HCA experience to co-ordinate, manage and run physical health clinics across Brighton and Hove in addition to supporting existing depot clinic services to carry out blood monitoring and health screening for clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from those who are highly motivated, and enthusiastic to work alongside our existing team. The role would suit someone who is resourceful and flexible with time management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would be expected to travel between our sites at Brighton General Hospital and Hove Polyclinic depending upon service needs, there is also a number of home visits across the city but the main base is Hove Polyclinic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The client group is from our community mental health services across Brighton and Hove. You will be working alongside another HCA as part of a supportive team. There will be regular high quality supervision, support and training to develop your skills in working with people who have severe and enduring mental illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Greg Coghlan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Lead Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Greg.Coghlan@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07471 218439&lt;/p&gt;
